<h2 class="bac"><a href="" title="Hide information"><img class="pclose" src="../images/clear.gif" alt="Hide information" title="Hide information"></a>Our Business</h2>
<div>
<h3 class="bac">Summary</h3>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Location: London.</li>
	<li>9 week, rotational programme from June - August.</li>
	<li>Fluency in English. A second European language may also be advantageous.</li>
</ul>
<p class="bac">The Quantitative Research Division is an integral component of the products the firm offers to clients. We provide clients with actionable investment ideas and solutions in the equity derivatives market. Research is based on quantitative analysis of the market environment, and requires a broad and deep understanding of the relevant derivative instruments and client risk/return profiles.</p>
<p class="bac">The summer programme focuses on quantitative research within the Research division and includes the equity derivatives, interest rate derivatives and commodities research groups. These groups produce client-driven quantitative research in some of the fastest growing areas in the global financial markets.</p>
</div></div>

<div class="expand">
<h2 class="bac"><a href="" title="Show information"><img class="popen" src="../images/clear.gif" alt="Show information" title="Show information"></a>Overview</h2>
<div>
<p class="bac nobr">As a Summer Intern within Global Quantitative Research, you will:</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Gain experience of working on impactful quantitative projects requiring strong analytical skills in a dynamic environment</li>
	<li>Develop a network of internal professionals, mentors, peers and possible future stakeholders across asset markets</li>
	<li>Develop the necessary confidence and experience to question and challenge senior team members/managers regarding investment advice, trade ideas and risks as well communicate and present complex concepts in clear and simple terms</li>
	<li>Gain insight into tradable financial instruments and structures within equity, interest rate and commodity derivatives markets</li>
</ul>
</div></div>

<div class="expand">
<h2 class="bac"><a href="" title="Show information"><img class="popen" src="../images/clear.gif" alt="Show information" title="Show information"></a>Training</h2>
<div>
<p class="bac nobr">Your internship will involve rotations amongst different desks within the business group which means you get a good overview of the business in detail. Training includes:</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>One week induction and training programme with classroom instruction</li>
	<li>A buddy and mentoring programme</li>
	<li>Summer Senior Speaker Series, featuring global  &amp; divisional presentations by top executives</li>
	<li>Opportunities to interact with senior bankers and network with peers</li>
	<li>Constructive feedback sessions through performance evaluations</li>
</ul>
</div></div>

<div class="expand">
<h2 class="bac"><a href="" title="Show information"><img class="popen" src="../images/clear.gif" alt="Show information" title="Show information"></a>Qualifications</h2>
<div>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>We&#39;re looking for a strong academic background in quantitative analysis (econometrics/ statistics/applied mathematics). A finance and economics or financial mathematics related subject at masters level is desirable.</li>
	<li>Fluency in English is essential and a second European language may also be advantageous</li>
	<li>Candidates must also show a long-term interest in the field of quantitative finance and demonstrate achievements towards their pursuit of a career in this field.</li>
	<li>Team-working, leadership and problem-solving skills, plus creativity are key qualities, as is the ability to work in a fast-paced environment, multi-task and interact with a variety of people</li>
</ul>
</div></div>

